column5: congrats Joeys!

That great St Croix muskie rod being raffled (and donated) by Ron Reyns for the profit of the Lake Simcoe Muskie Restoration Project has been won by none other than our very Joey!!!!  Ron will fill in the blanks here. In the meantime, congrats, girl. You deserve it and it was/IS a super cause.
Way to go Joey!!!!!
Congrats Joey, I assume you'll wear your muskie t-shirt when fishing with that rod?  lol  Mike
WTG Joey!!! Now go and get those big fishies!!!!
Hey Ron...that's not the deal we had.....  Looks like Fishhunter will be leaving Port Hope solo...your reservation has been cancelled.....  Congrats Joanne! Glad it's you at least !!

Holy crap, I can't believe it.  I rarely win anything.  This is fantastic.  You bet I'm gonna wear my beautiful shirt while fishing with that awesome rod.  Thank you so much.  Cheers everyone.  Woooooohoooooooooo.  This year is sure turning out to be a great one for me.  Maybe I can catch a fish now  Joey
Couldn't happen to a nicer OFNer...  Congrats Joey...  Mike
Way to go Joey!!
Quite the week you're having Joey. I'm happy for ya. Now go and catch some fish with your new prize..

Well, firstly I would like to thank everyone who generously donated towards a great project. Thinking of having an oportunity to fish for Muskie on Lake Simcoe in another 8 yrs sounds intriging. There are still a lot of learning curves to overcome in raising a wild Muskie, but every year will be better.  The effort put forward on your donations, raised another $555.00. This is a great start in what will be an ongoing project.  Congratulations Joey on winning the St. Croix Rod, I am sure you will enjoy years of use and abuse from it.  Once again, thanks to all who donated.
Oh, super sweet.  Congrats Jo.
Congrads Joey !!! Santa has come early for you...You must of been extra good this year !!!

I was under the impression Joey would get more presents by being naughty.  Wayne, sorry man. I just took all the tickets and tossed em into a pail. I got one of the guys wives to pull the name out. Hey, I can always sleep in a snowdrift.
WTG Joey, and congrats on the big win.  I've got several exactly the same  and their an excellent fish'n pole !!  Now, tell Paul you need a Calcutta  for Christmas to go with it and your all set
That's great Joey, Congrats!!!  Maureen
Congrats Joey, enjoy your new prize and best of luck with it.
Its funny you mention that Lew, as as soon as I told Paul about it he was on the puter looking up new reels    He was as excited as I was.  Joey
Congrats Joey
Congrats Joey,   it really is a sweet rod. Enjoy.  John
Good for you Joey....  your on a roll!!
WTG Joey!  Congrats again!
Marsha, Marsha, Marsha!  Joey, Joey, Joey!  Geeze, I'm starting to feel like Jan Brady here!  Just kidding, and way to go Joey!!!
....Wow, cogratulations Joey. Man am I ever glad we made that deal.
Congrats Joey and Good Luck with it.  Mike
